This paper is about deep neural networks and their deployment in embedded systems, which are topics that are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and architecture (cs.AR). The paper specifically focuses on a new method for discretizing both training and inference in deep neural networks, which is a technique that is relevant to all of these sub-categories. Therefore, it is likely that this paper could be classified under any of these sub-categories, with machine learning and artificial intelligence being the most likely due to the focus on deep neural networks.
